      • isWorthShowingInAutoPopup

        public boolean isWorthShowingInAutoPopup()
        Description copied from class: LookupElement
        Invoked when the completion autopopup contains only the items that exactly match the user-entered prefix to determine whether the popup should be closed to not get in the way when navigating through the code. Should return true if there's some meaningful information in this item's presentation that the user will miss if the autopopup is suddenly closed automatically. Java method parameters are a good example. For simple variables, there's nothing else interesting besides the variable name which is already entered in the editor, so the autopopup may be closed.
        Overrides:
        isWorthShowingInAutoPopup in class LookupElement

      • getPsiElement

        public PsiElement getPsiElement()
        Overrides:
        getPsiElement in class LookupElement
        Returns:
        a PSI element associated with this lookup element. It's used for navigation, showing quick documentation and sorting by proximity to the current location. The default implementation tries to extract PSI element from LookupElement.getObject() result.
